      {
        "question": "How accurate is the UPT? ",
        "answer": "Its accuracy is from 97 to 99% if follow all the conditions to take the test."
      },
      {
        "question": "Am I allowed to take the UPT too early? ",
        "answer": "Yes, taking the test too early can lead to positive or negative pregnancy syndrome results. It is advised to wait until after one’s expected menstrual cycle or once there are clear early pregnancy signs."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is it possible that the outcome of the test can be altered by some drugs or by some health issues? ",
        "answer": "Yes, certain medications and medical conditions can lead to misleading positive or negative results. Please speak to a qualified professional if you are experiencing any problems."
      },
      {
        "question": "What steps should I follow after I get a positive answer from the test? ",
        "answer": "If you get a positive indication, see a qualified healthcare provider at once for confirmatory checks regarding pregnancy, and initiate pre-natal healthcare."
      }
